  <!-- Section: Common Mistakes -->
  <section id="mistakes" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Missing Federal Police Registration</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">You must register with Federal Police within 90 days of arrival. Miss this and you'll face complications with visa renewal and exit.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Underestimating Safety Concerns</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Brazil has higher crime rates than many DNV destinations. Research neighborhoods, don't flash valuables, and use common sense. Most nomads stay safe with awareness.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Not Learning Portuguese</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">English is not widely spoken outside tourist areas. Basic Portuguese significantly improves your experience and is essential for daily life.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Expecting Fast Bureaucracy</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Brazilian bureaucracy is slow. Bank accounts, official processes, and paperwork take time. Build in patience and extra days.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Only Considering Rio/São Paulo</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Brazil is huge with diverse options. Florianópolis has tech scene and beaches; the Northeast is cheaper and beautiful; smaller cities offer unique experiences.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Skipping Insurance</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Insurance is mandatory, but also genuinely important. Private healthcare is good but not cheap. Don't risk large unexpected bills.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Healthcare in Brazil -->
