      <li><strong>Emergency room (private):</strong> $100-300</li>
      <li><strong>Dental cleaning:</strong> $30-60</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: FAQ -->
  <section id="faq" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I renew the Digital Nomad Visa?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes. Brazil's DNV can be renewed once for an additional year, giving you up to 2 years total. Apply for renewal before your first year expires.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need to speak Portuguese?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Not for the visa, but practically yes. English is limited outside tourist areas. Basic Portuguese is essential for daily life and significantly improves your experience.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Brazil safe for digital nomads?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Brazil has higher crime rates than many destinations. That said, thousands of expats live safely by choosing good neighborhoods, being aware, and not displaying wealth. Research your area carefully.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's the best city for digital nomads?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Florianópolis is the top nomad hub—tech scene, beaches, good infrastructure, safer than Rio/São Paulo. São Paulo has the biggest scene but is huge and urban. Rio offers iconic lifestyle but requires more safety awareness.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I pay taxes in Brazil?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          The Digital Nomad Visa doesn't automatically make you a tax resident. However, if you stay 183+ days in a 12-month period, you may trigger tax residency. Consult a Brazilian tax advisor.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What is a CPF and do I need one?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          The CPF is Brazil's tax ID number. It's not required for the visa but makes life much easier—you need it for bank accounts, phone contracts, and many services. It's free to obtain.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

